## DECLARATION REGARDING NOTICE (CRC 3.1203–3.1204)

### IN SUPPORT OF EX PARTE APPLICATION FOR ORDER SHORTENING TIME

I, **Michael James Romero**, declare:

1. **Identity and Capacity.** I am the Plaintiff in this action, appearing in pro per. I have personal knowledge of the facts set forth herein.

2. **Ex Parte Hearing Information.** I intend to appear **ex parte** in **Department R12** on **Thursday, November 13, 2025** at **9:00 a.m.** to request an **Order Shortening Time** on Plaintiff’s pending **Motion to Compel Defendant’s Deposition; Request for Monetary Sanctions; and Request for Limited Leave After Cutoff** and to set a condensed briefing schedule. I will not seek a merits ruling ex parte.

3. **Persons Notified.** On **[Notice Date]** at **[Time of Notice]**, I will provide ex parte notice to:
   **Randal P. Hannah, Esq.**
   **Law Office of Randal P. Hannah**
   **489 N. Central Ave., Upland, CA 91786**
   (counsel for Defendant **Megan Nicole Bentley**).

4. **Manner of Notice.** I will give notice **by email** to defense counsel identified above.

5. **Content of Notice.** My notice will state:
   (a) that I will appear ex parte on **Thursday, November 13, 2025 at 9:00 a.m.** in **Dept. R12** at **8303 Haven Avenue, Rancho Cucamonga, CA 91730**;
   (b) the **relief requested**: an **Order Shortening Time** on Plaintiff’s pending motion to compel Defendant’s deposition and a condensed briefing schedule;
   (c) that I will **not** seek a merits ruling at the ex parte; and
   (d) that any written opposition to the **ex parte** may be presented at the hearing.

6. **Compliance with Timing (CRC 3.1203).** Notice will be provided **no later than 10:00 a.m. on the court day before the ex parte appearance**.

7. **Whether Opposition Is Expected.** As of the execution of this declaration, opposition is **unknown**; I will promptly advise the Court at the ex parte hearing if counsel indicates an intent to oppose.

8. **Diligence / Efforts to Give Notice.** I will send the email notice described above and, if no immediate response is received, follow up as reasonable. Copies of my email notice, any responses, and call logs (if any) will be attached as **Exhibit A** when available.

9. **Service of Papers.** At the **first reasonable opportunity** after providing notice, I will **e‑file** the ex parte papers and **serve them by email** on defense counsel the same day. I will also reference the already‑filed **Motion to Compel** set for **February 11, 2026 at 9:00 a.m.**

10. **Hearing Location Confirmed.** My notice will identify the location **(Dept. R12, 8303 Haven Avenue, Rancho Cucamonga, CA 91730)** and that the Court may allow **remote appearance** subject to department procedures.

11. **Reservation Information.** The department **does not issue reservation numbers** for ex parte calendars; **none was issued**.

12. **Attachments.** Attached as **Exhibit A** will be true and correct copies of my notice communications and any responses (emails and confirmations). Additional proofs of service will be attached as **Exhibit B**.

I declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the State of California that the foregoing is true and correct.

Executed on **November 12, 2025**, at **Los Angeles, California**.

